\title{Coinflip structure}
\taxon{Definition}
\p{
  Let #{\cC} be a Markov category. A \em{coinflip structure} is a [internal midpoint algebra](efr-1XB5) structure on each #{A \in \cC}, which is natural in #{A}. In other words, it is a [midpoint algebra](efr-6W7X) structure on each homset #{\cC(X,Y)} so that both pre- and postcomposition are midpoint homomorphisms.
}